reference.Refstring: Arora, C., Sabetzadeh, M., & Briand, L. C. (2019). An empirical study on the potential usefulness of domain models for completeness checking of requirements. Empirical Software Engineering, 24(4), 2509-2539.

descriptions.definition: "Internal completeness is concerned with ensuring that a given requirements specification is closed with respect to the statements and inferences that can be made solely based on that specification"
"External completeness is concerned with ensuring that all the information that is pertinent to the definition of a system is found within the specification"
